		<title>18LOCAL INDUSTRY</title>
		<content> By far the dominant industry in the   
 area is that of mining. Manton        
 Colliery to the east of the town      
 employs 1180 men of which 900 work    
 underground. Worksop men also work in 
 other pits in the area.               
                                       
 Another large employer is Mansfield   
 Hosiery which employs around 650      
 workers.                              
                                       
 Other industries are glass bottle     
 manufacture, charcoal making, light   
 engineering and agriculture. Worksop  
 is surrounded by arable land which    
 grows cereals, potatoes, sugar beet   
 and rape.                             
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
